For OCP 4.20.21 and the mirror layout shown in your screenshot, try finding the release image like this:

oc adm release info \
  --registry-config pull-secret.json \
  bastion-sno.lab.ocp.lan:8443/ocp4/openshift4/openshift/release-images:4.20.21-x86_64

If that works, use:

export OPENSHIFT_INSTALL_RELEASE_IMAGE_OVERRIDE=bastion-sno.lab.ocp.lan:8443/ocp4/openshift4/openshift/release-images:4.20.21-x86_64

openshift-install agent create image --dir clusterconfigs

To verify the installer can get the RHCOS content offline:

oc adm release info \
  --image-for=machine-os-images \
  $OPENSHIFT_INSTALL_RELEASE_IMAGE_OVERRIDE

If it returns something like:

bastion-sno.lab.ocp.lan:8443/...@sha256:xxxxx

then the installer will extract the RHCOS artifacts from your mirrored release payload. No internet access and no separate ISO file in the registry are required.

If you're not sure of the exact tag, run:

skopeo list-tags \
docker://bastion-sno.lab.ocp.lan:8443/ocp4/openshift4/openshift/release-images

and paste the output. That will show the exact tag you should use for OPENSHIFT_INSTALL_RELEASE_IMAGE_OVERRIDE.
